  <li>
    <p>htop<br />
 htop is an interactive process viewer(similar to windowsâ€™ task manager).  Needless to say, it looks hot and in the mean time you can inspect processes ongoing.</p>

    <div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code> htop
</code></pre></div>    </div>

    <p><img src="/img/htop.png" alt="" /></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>banner<br />
 With this command, you can get nicely formatted text of asterisks.</p>

    <div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code> banner text
</code></pre></div>    </div>

    <p><img src="/img/banner.png" alt="" /></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>lolcat<br />
 lolcat provides rainbow coloring effect for text console display. Remember, it doesnt come pre-installed in your system. So install it from package manager your distro supports.</p>

    <div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code> <span class="nb">echo</span> <span class="s1">'text'</span> | lolcat
</code></pre></div>    </div>

    <p><img src="/img/lolcat.png" alt="" /></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>sl<br />
 sl generates a moving ASCII train. According to its man page, it is developed to cure habit of mistyping. When someone mistypes sl for ls, they suffer. You can combine sl with lolcat to generate rainbow colored train. :D</p>

    <div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code> sl 
</code></pre></div>    </div>
    <p><img src="/img/sl.png" alt="" /></p>
  </li>
